prompt: My ice cream shop was really busy today. It was 98 degrees and we sold 67 ice cream cones. We sold 15 more milkshakes than ice cream cones. How many milkshakes were sold?
summary: var1 = [find](ice cream cones sold) # 67, var2 = [find](milkshakes sold) # 67 + 15 = 82, [return](var2) # 82

prompt: The garment factory produces 665 sets of children's clothing, and the production of adult clothing is 7 times that of children's clothing. How many sets of adult clothing are produced?
summary: var1 = [find](number of sets of children's clothing) #665, var2 = [multiply](var1, 7) # 665 * 7 = 4655, [return](var2) # 4655

prompt: To build a road, the full length (3/4) has been built, which is exactly 30 kilometers. How many kilometers is the total length of this road?
summary: var1 = [find](length of built road) #30, var2 = [divide](var1, fraction(3,4)) # 30 / 0.75 = 40, [return](var2) # 40

prompt: After eating at the restaurant, Sally, Sam, and Alyssa decided to divide the bill evenly. If each person paid 45 dollars, what was the total of the bill?
summary: var1 = [find](number of people) #3, var2 = [multiply](var1, 45) #3 * 45 = 135, [return](var2) # 135

prompt: There are 142 pear trees in the orchard, and 12 times as many apple trees as pear trees. How many apple trees are there?
summary: var1 = [find](number of pear trees) #142, var2 = [multiply](var1, 12) # 142 x 12 = 1704, [return](var2) # 1704

prompt: Kelly had 56 apples. How many more apples does Kelly need to pick to have 105 apples altogether?
summary: var1 = [find](Kelly had apples) # 56, var2 = [find](apples Kelly needs to pick) # 105 - 56 # 105 - 56 = 49, [return](var2) # 49

prompt: The perimeter of an equilateral triangle is 54 cm. Find the length of each side of triangle.
summary: var1 = [find](perimeter) # 54, var2 = [divide](var1, 3) # 54 / 3 = 18, [return](var2) # 18

prompt: The tree planters planted 201 poplars this year, three times as many pine trees as poplars. How many pine trees did they plant?
summary: var1 = [find](number of poplars planted) #201, var2 = [multiply](var1, 3) # 201 * 3 = 603, [return](var2) # 603

prompt: The sixth grade students went to the garbage power station to visit and study. Each car can seat 58 people. It is known that there are 218 boys and 188 girls in the sixth grade. How many such buses are needed? (use comprehensive formula to answer)
summary: var1 = [find](total number of sixth grade students) #218 + 188 = 406, var2 = [find](number of buses needed) #use the comprehensive formula: [divide](var1, (seating capacity per bus)) with rounding up to the nearest whole number # [divide](406, 58) = 7 with rounding up, [return](var2) #7

prompt: The Smart Mart sells educational toys. They sold 45 science kits last week. The sold 9 fewer puzzles than science kits. How many puzzles did the Smart Mart sell?
summary: var1 = [find](science kits) # 45, var2 = [subtract](var1, 9) # 45 - 9 = 36, [return](var2) # 36

prompt: Sally has 6 blue balloons. Fred has 3 times more blue balloons than Sally. How many blue balloons does Fred have now?

prompt: The fruit store shipped 560 kilograms of apples, and the number of oranges shipped was 1.5 times that of apples. How many kilograms of oranges did the fruit store ship?

prompt: The school planted 45 poplars, 17 fewer willows than poplars, and 31 more metasequoias than willows. How many metasequoia trees are there?

prompt: Pamela bought 9.8 ounces of sugar, and she spilled 5.2 ounces of it on the floor. How much is left?

prompt: Aunt Zhao typed 108 words per minute, and she took about 15 minutes to type a manuscript. How many words are there in this manuscript?

prompt: Xiaodong's height is 116 cm, and his father's height is 176 cm. How many centimeters does Xiaodong need to grow to be as tall as his father?
summary: var1 = [find](Xiaodong's height) #116, var2 = [find](father's height) #176, var3 = [subtract](var2, var1) # 176 - 116 = 60, [return](var3) # 60

prompt: There are 10 stickers on a page. If you have 22 pages of stickers, how many stickers do you have?

prompt: I have 648 pencils. If I put 4 pencils in each pencil box, how many pencil boxes will I fill?

prompt: Carefully following a recipe, Kenny used exactly 0.16666666666666666 cup of oil and 1.1666666666666667 cups of water. How many cups of liquid did Kenny use in all?
Charles was curious about Greek mythology and so he read 8 pages a day of a 96-page book entitled "Greek Mythology: Fast Facts." How many days did it take Charles to finish the book?

prompt: Lexie has a lot of art materials. She needs to organize all these materials into containers. She counted her crayons and found out that she has 80 crayons which she will place in crayon boxes. Every crayon box can contain 8 crayons. How many crayon boxes does she need?

prompt: Daniel and his brother Ben went to their grandfather's farm for a few weeks of vacation. During their stay at the farm, they were asked to take care of the animals. One day, his grandfather asked if he could count the total number of sheep that they have. If there are 3 herds of sheep and each herd has 20 sheep, how many sheep do they have in total?
summary: var1 = [find](number of herds) # 3, var2 = [find](number of sheep per herd) # 20, var1 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 3 * 20 = 60, [return](var1) # 60

prompt: They also gathered paper to create some star-shaped papier-mache. If each star requires 20 pieces of paper and they had 680 pieces of paper, how many stars were they able to make?

prompt: After a week, Sofia did a survey to ask if the students liked the new menu. She found out that 235 students liked the new menu while 165 didn't. How many students took part in Sofia's survey?

prompt: A restaurant critic reviewed restaurants in Richmond and Yardley. In Richmond, the critic gave 14 positive reviews and 20 negative reviews. In Yardley, 12 of the reviews were positive and 17 were negative. In which city did the restaurant critic give a higher ratio of positive to negative reviews?

prompt: At the back of the zoo is a mountain where the birds can roam free in a natural habitat. The children saw 6 types of eagles living on each section of the mountain. If the mountain has 3 sections, how many types of eagles did the children see in total?

prompt: There are 253 tons of chemical fertilizers in the warehouse. After some of them are shipped out, the remaining (4/11) of the total amount is left. How many tons of chemical fertilizers are there in the warehouse at this time?
summary: var1 = [find](total amount of chemical fertilizers) #253, var2 = [find](fraction remaining after shipping) #(4/11), var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 253 * (4/11) = 92, [return](var3) # 92

prompt: The town of Milberg has 5256 grown-ups and 2987 children. How many people live in Milberg?
summary: var1 = [find](number of grown-ups) #5256, var2 = [find](number of children) #2987, var3 = [add](var1, var2) # 5256 + 2987 = 8243, [return](var3) # 8243

prompt: Nicole found an orange caterpillar and a green caterpillar in her backyard. The green caterpillar was 3 inches long, and the orange caterpillar was 1.1666666666666667 inches long. How much longer was the green caterpillar than the orange caterpillar?
summary: var1 = [find](length of green caterpillar) #3, var2 = [find](length of orange caterpillar) #1.1666666666666667, var3 = [subtract](var1, var2) # 3 - 1.1666666666666667 = 1.8333333333333333, [return](var3) # 1.8333333333333333

prompt: Ned gave away thirteen of his video games to a friend. Now Ned has six games. How many games did Ned have before he gave the games away?
summary: var1 = [find](left games) # 6, var2 = [find](given away games) # 13, var3 = [add](var1, var2) # 6 + 13 = 19, [return](var3) # 19

prompt: Emily sprinted to Timothy's house. It is 10 miles from Emily's house to Timothy's house. It took Emily 2 hours to get there. How fast did Emily go?
summary: var1 = [find](distance between Emily's and Timothy's house) #10, var2 = [find](time taken by Emily) #2, var3 = [divide](var1, var2) # 10 / 2 = 5, [return](var3) # 5

prompt: An envelope from the post office is 4 inches wide and 4 inches long. What is the area of the envelope?
summary: var1 = [find](width) # 4, var2 = [find](length) # 4, var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 4 * 4 = 16, [return](var3) # 16

prompt: A store has forty-nine shirts. After selling some there were twenty-eight left. How many did they sell?
summary: var1 = [find](total shirts) # 49, var2 = [find](left shirts) # 28, var3 = [subtract](var1, var2) # 49 - 28 = 21, [return](var3) # 21

prompt: An elephant weighs 5.1 tons, which is 15 times the weight of a cattle. How many tons does a cattle weigh?
summary: var1 = [find](weight of elephant in tons) #5.1, var2 = [find](ratio of elephant weight to cattle weight) #15, var3 = [divide](var1, var2) # 5.1 / 15 = 0.34, [return](var3) # 0.34

prompt: The school bought a rope with a length of 27.5 meters. After cutting it into 9 skipping ropes of the same length, there are 5 meters left. How many meters is the average length of each skipping rope?
summary: var1 = [find](total length of rope) #27.5, var2 = [find](number of skipping ropes) #9, var3 = [divide]([subtract](var1, 5), var2) # (27.5 - 5) / 9 = 2.5, [return](var3) # 2.5

prompt: A pair of trousers is 28.5 yuan, and the price of a jacket is 1.8 times that. How much does it cost to make a set of such clothes?
summary: var1 = [find](price of trousers) #28.5, var2 = [multiply](var1, 1.8) # 28.5 * 1.8 = 51.3, var3 = [add](var1, var2) # 28.5 + 51.3 = 79.8, [return](var3) # 79.8

prompt: Frank had forty-two pieces of candy. If he put them into bags with seven pieces in each bag, how many bags would he have?
summary: var1 = [find](total candy) # 42, var2 = [find](candy per bag) # 7, var3 = [divide](var1, var2) # 42 / 7 = 6, [return](var3) # 6

prompt: Paco had 93 cookies. Paco ate 15 of them. How many cookies did Paco have left?
summary: var1 = [find](number of cookies Paco had) # 93, var2 = [find](number of cookies Paco ate) # 15, var3 = [subtract](var1, var2) # 93 - 15 = 78, [return](var3) # 78

prompt: At Lindsey's Vacation Wear, 0.375 of the garments are bikinis, and 0.25 are trunks. What fraction of the garments are either bikinis or trunks?
summary: var1 = [find](fraction of garments that are bikinis) #0.375, var2 = [find](fraction of garments that are trunks) #0.25, var3 = [add](var1, var2) # 0.375 + 0.25 = 0.625, [return](var3) #0.625

prompt: The library has 75 science books. The second graders borrowed 18 of them. How many science books are left?
summary: var1 = [find](library science books) # 75, var2 = [find](borrowed books) # 18, var3 = [subtract](var1, var2) # 75 - 18 = 57, [return](var3) # 57

prompt: Xiaohong conducted a survey and statistics on the way students in lower grades went to school. There were 135 students who were picked up by their parents, accounting for 90% of the total number of people surveyed. How many people did Xiao Hong investigate?
summary: var1 = [find](percentage of students picked up by parents) #90%, var2 = [find](number of students picked up by parents) #135, var3 = [divide](var2, var1) # 135 / 0.9 = 150, [return](var3) # 150

prompt: Teacher Li wrote 3 popular science stories, and received a manuscript fee of 3,400 yuan. The part exceeding 800 yuan is subject to 14% personal income tax. How much tax should Teacher Li pay?
summary: var1 = [find](manuscript fee) #3,400, var2 = [find](amount exceeding 800 yuan) #2,600, var3 = [multiply](var2, 0.14) # 2,600 * 0.14 = 364, [return](var3) # 364

prompt: The fruit shop shipped 36 boxes of apples, each weighing 15 kilograms. How many kilograms are the apples in total?
summary: var1 = [find](number of boxes of apples) #36, var2 = [find](weight of each box of apples) #15, var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 36 * 15 = 540, [return](var3) # 540

prompt: James rode 80 miles at 16 miles per hour. How long did James ride?
summary: var1 = [find](distance James rode) #80, var2 = [find](speed of James) #16, var3 = [divide](var1, var2) # 80 / 16 = 5, [return](var3) # 5

prompt: Grandma Wang has 59 roosters, 77 hens, and 85 chicks. How many roosters and hens does Grandma Wang have?
summary: var1 = [find](number of roosters) #59, var2 = [find](number of hens) #77, var3 = [add](var1, var2) # 59 + 77 = 136, [return](var3) # 136

prompt: Colton has 16 blue marbles and 8 white ones. If he wants to place them in identical groups without any marbles left over, what is the greatest number of groups Colton can make?
summary: var1 = [find]("blue marbles") # 16, var2 = [find]("white marbles") # 8, var3 = [find_gcd](var1, var2) # GCD(16,8) = 8, [return](var3) # 8

prompt: After eating at the restaurant, Mary, Nancy, and Fred decided to divide the bill evenly. Nancy did not have dessert. If each person paid 33 dollars, what was the total of the bill ?
summary: var1 = [find](people paying) # 3, var2 = [find](amount paid by each person) # 33, var1 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 3 * 33 = 99, [return](var1) # 99

prompt: A chef had five potatoes to make fries with, but he only used three of them. How many potatoes does he still have?
summary: var1 = [find](total potatoes) # 5, var2 = [find](used potatoes) # 3, var3 = [subtract](var1, var2) # 5 - 3 = 2, [return](var3) # 2

prompt: Primary and secondary schools in Xincheng carried out waste paper recycling activities, and a total of 87.5 tons of waste paper were recycled. The recycling rate of recycled paper produced from waste paper is 80%. How many tons of recycled paper can these recycled waste paper produce?
summary: var1 = [find](total weight of waste paper recycled) #87.5, var2 = [find](recycling rate of recycled paper) #0.8, var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 87.5 * 0.8 = 70, [return](var3) # 70

prompt: Bridget has 4 Skittles. Henry has 4 Skittles. If Henry gives all of his Skittles to Bridget, how many Skittles will Bridget have?
summary: var1 = [find](number of Skittles Bridget has) #4, var2 = [find](number of Skittles Henry has) #4, var3 = [add](var1, var2) # 4 + 4 = 8, [return](var3) # 8

prompt: Recently, the postal service sold stamps with famous people pictured on them. They sold 578,833 color stamps, as well as 523,776 black-and-white ones. About how many stamps did they sell?
summary: var1 = [find](color stamps) # 578833, var2 = [find](black-and-white stamps) # 523776, var1 = [add](var1, var2), [return](var1) # 1102609

prompt: Stanley ran 0.4 of a mile and walked 0.2 of a mile. How much farther did Stanley run than walk?
summary: var1 = [find](distance Stanley ran) #0.4, var2 = [find](distance Stanley walked) #0.2, var3 = [subtract](var1, var2) # 0.4 - 0.2 = 0.2, [return](var3) # 0.2

prompt: There are 8 calories in a candy bar. How many calories are there in 3 candy bars?
summary: var1 = [find](calories in one candy bar) #8, var2 = [find](number of candy bars) #3, var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 8 * 3 = 24, [return](var3) # 24

prompt: A train has 9 carriages, and each carriage has 108 seats. How many seats are there in this train?
summary: var1 = [find](number of carriages) #9, var2 = [find](number of seats in each carriage) #108, var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 9 * 108 = 972, [return](var3) # 972

prompt: Isabel had sixty-eight pieces of candy. Her friend gave her twenty-five more pieces. How many pieces of candy did Isabel have total?
summary: var1 = [find](starting candy) # 68, var2 = [find](new candy) # 25, var1 = [add](var1, var2) # 68 + 25 = 93, [return](var1) # 93

prompt: A video uploaded had 18 'up votes'. If the ratio of 'up votes' to 'down votes' was 9:2, how many 'down votes' did the video get?
summary: var1 = [find](up votes) # 18, var2 = [divide](var1, 9), var3 = [multiply](var2, 2) # (18 / 9) * 2 = 4, [return](var3) # 4

prompt: There are 336 students in a school. If the school has 7 grades and each grade had the same number of students, how many students were in each grade?
summary: var1 = [find](students) # 336, var2 = [find](grades) # 7, var3 = [divide](var1, var2) # 336 / 7 = 48, [return](var3) # 48

prompt: A certain elementary school bought 120 story books, which accounted for exactly 4/9 of the books bought. How many books did the school buy in total?
summary: var1 = [find](number of story books bought) #120, var2 = [find](fraction of total books that story books represent) #4 / 9, var3 = [divide](var1, var2) # 120 / (4/9) = 270, [return](var3) # 270

prompt: Ben on the other hand, was asked to count the number of cows that they have. He saw that there are a total of 40 cows for every cow herd. How many cows do they have in total if there are 8 cow herds in the farm?
summary: var1 = [find](number of cow herds) # 8, var2 = [find](number of cows per herd) # 40, var1 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 8 * 40 = 320, [return](var1) # 320

prompt: In a high jump competition, Zhang Min jumped 0.9 meters, Xiao Hong jumped 0.05 meters lower than Zhang Min, and Li Hai jumped 0.15 meters higher than Xiao Hong. How many meters did Li Hai jump?
summary: var1 = [find](height of Zhang Min's jump) #0.9, var2 = [subtract](var1, 0.05) # 0.9 - 0.05 = 0.85, var3 = [add](var2, 0.15) # 0.85 + 0.15 = 1, [return](var3) # 1

prompt: Chris gave his 35 friends 12 pieces of candy each. How many pieces of candy did Chris give his friends?
summary: var1 = [find](friends of Chris) # 35, var2 = [find](candy per friend) # 12, var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 35 * 12 = 420, [return](var3) # 420

prompt: Shannon, Brenda's neighbor, joined Brenda in making bracelets. She brought 48 heart-shaped stones and wanted to have 8 of this type of stone in each of the bracelet she makes. How many bracelets with heart-shaped stones can Shannon make?
summary: var1 = [find](heart-shaped stones) # 48, var2 = [find](stones per bracelet) # 8, var1 = [divide](var1, var2) # 48 / 8 = 6, [return](var1) # 6

prompt: Zhenyue Computer City shipped a batch of new computers, including 140 notebook computers, accounting for (7/18) of the total number of newly shipped computers. How many new computers are there in total?
summary: var1 = [find](number of notebook computers) #140, var2 = [find](fraction of notebook computers in total) #(7/18), var3 = [divide](var1, var2) # 140 / (7/18) = 360, [return](var3) # 360

prompt: Candies come in packages of 4. Shirley ate 10 candies. How many candies does she have left?
summary: var1 = [find]("candies") # 10, var2 = [find]("package size") # 4, var3 = [mod](var1, var2) # 10 % 4 = 2, [return](var3) # 2

prompt: A waiter had eighteen customers. If six left, how many customers would the waiter still have?
summary: var1 = [find](total customers) # 18, var2 = [find](left customers) # 6, var3 = [subtract](var1, var2) # 18 - 6 = 12, [return](var3) # 12

prompt: Xiao Ming reads a storybook and has already read 35 pages, which is exactly equivalent to (7/11) of the whole book. How many pages does this storybook have?
summary: var1 = [find](percentage of book read) #7/11, var2 = [find](pages read) #35, var3 = [multiply](float(var2), float(1.0/var1)) # 35 * (1 / (7/11)) = 55, [return](var3) # 55

prompt: Cody had a bag of marbles. Later he gave five to his brother. Now Cody has seven marbles. How many marbles did Cody have to start with?
summary: var1 = [find](current marbles) # 7, var2 = [find](given marbles) # 5, var3 = [add](var1, var2) # 7 + 5 = 12, [return](var3) # 12

prompt: Lastly, Andrew tried to compute his expenses for the game night. If he spent $9.00 for each game they played and they played a total of 5 games, how much money did he spend that night?

prompt: The sum of three consecutive odd numbers is 69. What is the smallest of the three numbers?
summary: var1 = [find](sum of three consecutive odd numbers) #69, var2 = [divide](var1, 3) # 69 / 3 = 23, var3 = [subtract](var2, 2) # 23 - 2 = 21, [return](var3) # 21

prompt: Their next destination is Lake Erie. Still in a contest, Hazel caught 48 different fishes while her father caught 46. How many fishes did they catch in Lake Erie?

prompt: There are 50 female athletes participating in the school track and field competition, and the number of male athletes is 80% more than that of female athletes. How many male players are there?

prompt: Xiaoming's mother went to the street to sell cabbage. She sold 45.6 kilograms in the morning and 32.4 kilograms in the afternoon. The total price was 117 yuan. How much is the average price per kilogram of cabbage?

prompt: A garden has 52 rows and 15 columns of bean plants. How many plants are there in all?

prompt: Since the result of the vote was close, it was decided that they will balance the menu with both meat and vegetables. This decision was agreed upon by 154 third grade students and 237 fourth grade students. How many students agreed with the decision?

prompt: Mrs. Wong had 30 Valentines. She gave 8 Valentines to her children. How many does she have left?
summary: var1 = [find](total number of Valentines) #30, var2 = [find](number of Valentines given to children) #8, var3 = [subtract](var1, var2) # 30 - 8 = 22, [return](var3) # 22

prompt: A pile of sand was used to build a house (2/5), exactly 4 tons were used. How many tons is this pile of sand?
summary: var1 = [find](total weight of sand used) #4, var2 = [find](fraction of pile used for house) #2/5 or 0.4, var3 = [divide](var1, var2) # 4 / 0.4 = 10, [return](var3) # 10

prompt: 14 red plums and four green plums are in the basket. How many plums are in the basket?
summary: var1 = [find](red plums) # 14, var2 = [find](green plums) # 4, var3 = [add](var1, var2) # 14 + 4 = 18, [return](var3) # 18

prompt: A train traveled from Taicheng to Haikou City for 12 hours, traveling 108 kilometers per hour. How many kilometers are these two places apart?
summary: var1 = [find](time of travel) #12, var2 = [find](speed of train) #108, var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 12 * 108 = 1296, [return](var3) #1296

prompt: A panda weighs 75 kilograms, and a baby elephant weighs 20 kilograms less than 12 times that of a panda. How many kilograms does a baby elephant weigh?

prompt: The students borrowed some footballs, and now there are 24 left, which happens to be 3/5 of all the footballs. How many footballs are there in total?

prompt: The road between A and B is 150 kilometers long. A car drives from city A to city B, and travels the entire distance (3/5). How many kilometers does the car leave city A?

prompt: There were forty-seven bales of hay in the barn and forty bales in the shed. Benny stacked more bales in the barn today. There are now eighty-two bales of hay in the barn. How many bales did he store in the barn ?
summary: var1 = [find](original hay in barn) # 47, var2 = [find](final hay in barn) # 82, var1 = [subtract](var2, var1) # 82 - 47 = 35, [return](var1) # 35

prompt: Jane has 28 old brown sheets of drawing paper and 27 old yellow sheets of drawing paper. How many pieces of drawing paper does she have?
summary: var1 = [find](number of old brown sheets of drawing paper) #28, var2 = [find](number of old yellow sheets of drawing paper) #27, var3 = [add](var1, var2) # 28 + 27 = 55, [return](var3) # 55

prompt: After the price of a piece of clothing is reduced by 20%, the price is 184 yuan. How much is the original price of this piece of clothing?
summary: var1 = [find](discount percentage) #20%, var2 = [find](reduced price) #184 yuan, var3 = [divide](var2, (1 - (var1/100))) # 184 / (1 - (20/100)) = 230 yuan, [return](var3) # 230

prompt: Brad has 17 balloons. 8 balloons are red, and the rest are green. How many green balloons does Brad have?
summary: var1 = [find](total number of balloons) #17, var2 = [find](number of red balloons) #8, var3 = [subtract](var1, var2) # 17 - 8 = 9, [return](var3) # 9

prompt: There were ninety-eight onions on the shelf. Sixty-five were sold. How many onions is there on the shelf now?

prompt: Wendy bought 84 inches of ribbon. She used 46 inches to wrap presents. How much ribbon did Wendy have left?
summary: var1 = [find](ribbon bought) # 84, var2 = [find](ribbon used) # 46, var3 = [subtract](var1, var2) # 84 - 46 = 38, [return](var3) # 38

prompt: Third-grade students went to a concert in 8 buses. Each bus took 45 students. How many students went to the concert?
summary: var1 = [find](number of buses) #8, var2 = [find](number of students per bus) #45, var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 8 * 45 = 360, [return](var3) # 360

prompt: Sara has 3 green and 5 red marbles. Tom has 4 green marbles. How many green marbles do they have in total?

prompt: Adam has $5.00 to buy an airplane that costs $4.28. How much change will he get?

prompt: While playing a game Kaleb had ninety-eight lives. After losing some lives he had seventy-three left. How many lives did Kaleb lose?

prompt: To welcome the school celebration, the students made 24 yellow flags, which is 60% of the red flags. How many red flags were made?

prompt: Each day, the polar bear at Richmond's zoo eats 0.2 buckets of trout and 0.4 buckets of salmon. How many buckets of fish does the polar bear eat daily?

prompt: Jerry's freezer had 30 ice cubes in it. If he had to get ice for 6 cups, how many pieces should he put in each cup to make them have the same amount?

prompt: The mini library also has a section for the classics. If Jack has a collection of 6 classic authors, with each author having 33 books, how many books does he have in the classics section?
summary: var1 = [find](books per author) # 33, var2 = [find](number of authors) # 6, var1 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 33 * 6 = 198, [return](var1) # 198

prompt: One barrel of oil is used up (2/5), and there are 48 kilograms left. How much kilogram does this barrel of oil originally weigh?

prompt: In preparation for a party, Brant is putting desserts onto platters. The chocolate cake is cut into 15 pieces and the cheesecake is cut into 6 pieces. If he wants to prepare identical platters without having any cake left over, what is the greatest number of platters he can prepare?

prompt: Each of farmer Cunningham's 6048 lambs is either black or white. There are 193 white ones. How many of Farmer Cunningham's lambs are black?

prompt: Milford Lake was originally blue because it only had 809 algae plants. Now there are 3263 algae plants, and the lake has turned green. How many more algae plants are in Milford Lake now?

prompt: There are 37 short bushes and 30 tall trees currently in the park. Park workers will plant 20 short bushes today. How many short bushes will the park have when the workers are finished?
summary: var1 = [find](initial number of short bushes) #37, var2 = [find](number of short bushes to be planted) #20, var3 = [add](var1, var2) # 37 + 20 = 57, [return](var3) # 57

prompt: There are 4 children in the classroom. Each student will get 2 pencils. How many pencils will the teacher have to give out?

prompt: Tom was at the beach for 5 days and found 7 seashells every day. How many seashells did Tom find during the beach trip?

prompt: Sammy has 9 math problems to do for homework. He has already finished 2 of them. How many math problems does Sammy have left?

prompt: They entered the circus tent and saw that there are four seating sections for the audience. If each section can accommodate 246 people, how many people can the tent accommodate in total?
summary: var1 = [find](people per section) # 246, var2 = [find](number of sections) # 4, var1 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 246 * 4 = 984, [return](var1) # 984

prompt: There were 46 passengers on the bus. 19 passengers got off at the first stop. 15 passengers got off at the second stop. How many passengers were left on the bus?
summary: var1 = [find](initial passengers) # 46, var2 = [subtract](var1, 19) # 46 - 19 = 27, var3 = [subtract](var2, 15) # 27 - 15 = 12, [return](var3) # 12

prompt: On Arbor Day, the students planted 150 trees, and (1/3) were planted on the first day, among which (2/5) were planted by the sixth graders. How many trees were planted on the first day of sixth grade?
summary: var1 = [find](total number of trees planted) #150, var2 = [multiply](1/3, var1) # 1/3 * 150 = 50, var3 = [multiply](2/5, var2) # 2/5 * 50 = 20, [return](var3) # 20

prompt: Xiaohong walks 65 meters per minute, and walks from home to school for 12 minutes. How many meters is the distance from Xiaohong's home to school?
summary: var1 = [find](speed of Xiaohong walking) #65, var2 = [find](time taken to walk from home to school) #12, var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 65 * 12 = 780, [return](var3) # 780

prompt: Aliyah had some candy to give to her 4 children. She first took 10 pieces for herself and then evenly divided the rest among her children. Each child received 2 pieces. With how many pieces did she start?
summary: var1 = [find](number of Aliyah's children) #4, var2 = [multiply](var1, 2) # 4 * 2 = 8 (total number of candy pieces given to children), var3 = [add](var2, 10) # 8 + 10 = 18 (total number of candy pieces Aliyah had), [return](var3) # 18

prompt: Andrew is having his friends over for game night. So he decided to prepare the snacks and the games. He started by making mini sandwiches. If he has 4 friends coming over and he made 3 sandwiches for each one of them, how many sandwiches did he make in total?
summary: var1 = [find](number of friends coming over) # 4, var2 = [find](sandwich per person) # 3, var1 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 4 * 3 = 12, [return](var1) # 12

prompt: Nancy starts with 91 bottle caps. She finds another 88. How many bottle caps does Nancy end with?
summary: var1 = [find](initial number of bottle caps) #91, var2 = [find](number of additional bottle caps found) #88, var3 = [add](var1, var2) # 91 + 88 = 179, [return](var3) # 179

prompt: The tallest giraffe at the zoo is 96 inches tall. There are 14 adult giraffes at the zoo. The shortest giraffe is 68 inches. How much taller is the bigger giraffe?
summary: var1 = [find](tallest giraffe) # 96, var2 = [find](shortest giraffe) # 68, var3 = [subtract](var1, var2) # 96 - 68 = 28, [return](var3) # 28

prompt: There are 48 rabbits in the breeding group, and 4 rabbits are placed in each cage. How many cages are needed in total?
summary: var1 = [find](number of rabbits in breeding group) #48, var2 = [find](number of rabbits per cage) #4, var3 = [divide](var1, var2) # 48 / 4 = 12, [return](var3) # 12

prompt: There are 192 willows by the river, equal to (3/4) of poplars. How many poplars are there?
summary: var1 = [find](number of willows) #192, var2 = [find](fraction of poplars equivalent to willows) #(3/4), var3 = [divide](var1, var2) # 192 / (3/4) = 256, [return](var3) # 256

prompt: There are 200 apple trees in the orchard, and the number of pear trees is 20% more than the number of apples. How many pear trees are there?
summary: var1 = [find](number of apple trees) #200, var2 = [multiply](var1, 0.2) # 200 * 0.2 = 40, var3 = [add](var1, var2) # 200 + 40 = 240, [return](var3) # 240

prompt: Lucy put sixty-eight shells in her bucket. She found some more shells and now she has eighty-nine shells. How many more did she find?
summary: var1 = [find](Lucy's shells) # 68, var2 = [find](shells found) # 89 - 68, var3 = [subtract](89, var1) # 89 - 68 = 21, [return](var3) # 21

prompt: Four girls were home all day one weekend preparing homemade treats. Anna made 33 blueberry cookies. If she shares this equally among her four friends, how many will each receive?
summary: var1 = [find](blueberry cookies) # 33, var2 = [find](friends) # 4, var1 = [divide](var1, var2) # 33 / 4 = 8 with a remainder of 1, [return](var1) # 8

prompt: It takes 11 hours to fly from A to B, and the plane flies 735 kilometers per hour. How many kilometers are there between A and B?
summary: var1 = [find](flight time in hours) #11, var2 = [find](speed of plane in km/hr) #735, var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 11 * 735 = 8085, [return](var3) # 8085

prompt: The price of a piece of clothing is 80 yuan after hitting 0.8. How much is the original price of this piece of clothing?
summary: var1 = [find](final price of clothing) #80, var2 = [find](discount percentage) #0.8, var3 = [divide](var1, var2) # 80 / 0.8 = 100, [return](var3) # 100

prompt: The distance between Honghong’s home and school is 0.32 kilometers, and the distance between Liangliang’s home and school is five times that of Honghong’s home. How far is Liangliang's home from school?
summary: var1 = [find](distance between Honghong's home and school) #0.32, var2 = [find](multiplier for Liangliang's distance) #5, var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 0.32 * 5 = 1.6, [return](var3) # 1.6

prompt: Elizabeth went to the salon and had 0.375 of an inch of hair cut off. The next day she went back and asked for another 0.5 of an inch to be cut off. How much hair did she have cut off in all?
summary: var1 = [find](amount of hair cut the first day) #0.375, var2 = [find](amount of hair cut the second day) #0.5, var3 = [add](var1, var2) # 0.375 + 0.5 = 0.875, [return](var3) # 0.875

prompt: A sheep weighs 25 kilograms, and a cow weighs 14 times that of a sheep. How many kilograms does a cow weigh more than a sheep?
summary: var1 = [find](weight of sheep) #25, var2 = [multiply](var1, 14) # 25 * 14 = 350, var3 = [subtract](var2, var1) # 350 - 25 = 325, [return](var3) # 325

prompt: Xiaohong's weight is 25 kg, and grandma's weight is three times hers. How many kilograms does grandma and Xiaohong weigh together?
summary: var1 = [find](Xiaohong's weight) #25, var2 = [multiply](var1, 3) # 25 * 3 = 75, var3 = [add](var1, var2) # 25 + 75 = 100, [return](var3) # 100

prompt: Jason has 3 Pokemon cards. Benny bought 2 of Jason's Pokemon cards. How many Pokemon cards does Jason have now?
summary: var1 = [find](number of Pokemon cards Jason has) # 3, var2 = [find](number of Pokemon cards Benny bought) # 2, var3 = [subtract](var1, var2) # 3 - 2 = 1, [return](var3) # 1

prompt: Xiaohua has 6 story books, and the number of comic books is 8 times that of the story books. How many comic books does Xiaohua have?
summary: var1 = [find](number of story books) #6, var2 = [find](ratio of comic books to story books) #8, var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 6 * 8 = 48, [return](var3) # 48

prompt: It's New Year's Eve. Benjamin and his family went to New York City to take part in the celebration that is going to take place later that night. Before the evening celebrations, Benjamin wanted to see some of the famous places in NYC first. From the hotel, he walked 234 steps to the nearest restaurant then another 378 steps to Central Park. How many steps did he take to get to Central Park from the hotel?
summary: var1 = [find](steps to restaurant) # 234, var2 = [find](steps to Central Park) # 378, var1 = [add](var1, var2) # 234 + 378 = 612, [return](var1) # 612

prompt: In the first half of a trivia game Kaleb scored forty-three points. In the second half he scored twenty-three points. How many points did he score total?
summary: var1 = [find](first half points) # 43, var2 = [find](second half points) # 23, var1 = [add](var1, var2) # 43 + 23 = 66, [return](var1) # 66

prompt: Haley grew sixteen trees in her backyard. After a typhoon five died. How many trees does she have left?
summary: var1 = [find](total trees) # 16, var2 = [find](dead trees) # 5, var3 = [subtract](var1, var2) # 16 - 5 = 11, [return](var3) # 11

prompt: Lewis then went to see the oranges being harvested. Lewis found out that they harvest 83 sacks per day. How many sacks of oranges will they have after 6 days of harvest?
summary: var1 = [find](sacks harvested per day) #83, var2 = [find](days of harvest) #6, var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 83 * 6 = 498, [return](var3) # 498

prompt: Corey earns extra money finding lost golf balls. His goal is to find 48 golfballs every weekend. He found 16 golf balls on Saturday. He found 18 more golf balls on Sunday. How many more golf balls does Corey need to find to reach his goal?
summary: var1 = [find](goal golf balls) # 48, var2 = [add](16, 18) # 16 + 18 = 34, var3 = [subtract](var1, var2) # 48 - 34 = 14, [return](var3) # 14

prompt: A marine biologist measured one fish that was 0.3 of a foot long and a second fish that was 0.2 of a foot long. How much longer was the first fish?
summary: var1 = [find](length of fish 1) #0.3, var2 = [find](length of fish 2) #0.2, var3 = [subtract](var1, var2) # 0.3 - 0.2 = 0.1, [return](var3) # 0.1

prompt: Mr. Guzman bought 48 doughnuts packed equally into 4 boxes. How many doughnuts were in each box?
summary: var1 = [find](doughnuts) # 48, var2 = [find](boxes) # 4, var3 = [divide](var1, var2) # 48 / 4 = 12, [return](var3) # 12

prompt: The zookeeper has 68 fish to feed to the penguins. 19 penguins have already gotten a fish. The zoo has 36 penguins. How many more penguins need to get a fish?
summary: var1 = [find](penguins fed) # 19, var2 = [find](penguins) # 36, var3 = [subtract](var2, var1) # 36 - 19 = 17, [return](var3) # 17

prompt: A certain county afforested 1260 hectares last year, exceeding the original plan (1/5). How many hectares were originally planned for afforestation?
summary: var1 = [find](hectares afforested) #1260, var2 = [find](exceeded plan fraction) #1/5 or 0.2, var3 = [divide](var1, (1 + var2)) # 1260 / (1 + 0.2) = 1050, [return](var3) # 1050

prompt: There are 147 students in the fourth grade, the number of fifth grade students is the fourth grade (2/3), and the number of sixth grade students is equivalent to the fifth grade (6/7). How many students are there in grade six?
summary: var1 = [find](number of fourth grade students) #147, var2 = [multiply](var1, 2/3) # 147 * 2/3 = 98, var3 = [multiply](var2, 6/7) # 98 * 6/7 = 84, [return](var3) # 84

prompt: There are 450 boys in the railway primary school, and the number of girls is as many as boys (4/5). How many students are there in this school?
summary: var1 = [find](number of boys) #450, var2 = [find](ratio of girls to boys) #4/5, var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 450 * 4/5 = 360, var4 = [add](var1, var3) # 450 + 360 = 810, [return](var4) # 810

prompt: There are 4 tigers in the zoo, with a total weight of 1120 kg. There is an elephant, which is 4320 kg heavier than the average weight of a tiger. How much does this elephant weigh?
summary: var1 = [find](number of tigers) #4, var2 = [find](total weight of tigers) #1120, var3 = [divide](var2, var1) # 1120 / 4 = 280, var4 = [add](var3, 4320) # 280 + 4320 = 4600, [return](var4) # 4600

prompt: At the arcade Amy had 6 tickets she saved from the last time she went. This time she played a game 7 times and earned 5 tickets each time she played. How many tickets does she have now?
summary: var1 = [find](starting tickets) # 6, var2 = [find](games played) # 7, var3 = [find](tickets earned per game) # 5, var2 = var2 * var3 # 7 * 5 = 35, var1 = [add](var1, var2) # 6 + 35 = 41, [return](var1) # 41

prompt: The truck travels 80 kilometers per hour, and the car travels (1/4) more distance per hour than the truck. How many kilometers does the car travel per hour?
summary: var1 = [find](speed of truck) # 80, var2 = [find](fraction more distance car travels per hour) # 1/4, var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 80 * 1/4 = 20, var4 = [add](var1, var3) # 80 + 20 = 100, [return](var4) # 100

prompt: The orchard has planted 200 fruit trees this year, and the survival rate is 98%. How many trees died.
summary: var1 = [find](number of fruit trees planted) #200, var2 = [find](survival rate) #98%, var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 200 * 0.98 = 196, var4 = [subtract](var1, var3) # 200 - 196 = 4, [return](var4) # 4

prompt: Xiaoling participates in a mathematics competition, the total number of questions in the whole paper is 18, and Xiaoling only does the correct number of questions (8/9). How many questions did Xiao Ling do wrong?
summary: var1 = [find](total number of questions) #18, var2 = [find](correct number of questions) #8/9, var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 18 * 8/9 = 16, var4 = [subtract](var1, var3) # 18 - 16 = 2, [return](var4) # 2

prompt: The school bought 300 floppy disks and bought 20% less CDs than floppy disks. How many CDs did they buy?
summary: var1 = [find](number of floppy disks bought) #300, var2 = [find](percentage of CDs bought) #20%, var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 300 * 20% = 60, var4 = [subtract](var1, var3) # 300 - 60 = 240, [return](var4) # 240

prompt: There are 650 students in Yangfang Boarding Primary School, and 96% of them are insured. How many students are not insured?
summary: var1 = [find](total number of students) #650, var2 = [find](percentage of insured students) #96%, var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 650 * 96% = 624, var4 = [subtract](var1, var3) # 650 - 624 = 26, [return](var4) # 26

prompt: The original price of a TV is 4,500 yuan, and the discount is 0.9 during the "October" festival. How much can you save by buying such a TV?
summary: var1 = [find](original price of TV) #4,500, var2 = [find](discount rate) #0.9, var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 4,500 * 0.9 = 4,050, var4 = [subtract](var1, var3) # 4,500 - 4,050 = 450, [return](var4) # 450

prompt: 2400 eggs were used to incubate chicks, but 5% of them failed to hatch. How many chicks hatched?
summary: var1 = [find](number of eggs used) #2400, var2 = [find](percentage of eggs that failed to hatch) #5, var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 2400 * 5 / 100 = 120, var4 = [subtract](var1, var3) # 2400 - 120 = 2280, [return](var4) # 2280

prompt: When a number is divided by 5, the quotient is 8 and the remainder is 3. Find this number =?
summary: var1 = [find](quotient) #8, var2 = [find](remainder) #3, var3 = [multiply](var1, 5) # 8 * 5 = 40, var4 = [add](var3, var2) # 40 + 3 = 43, [return](var4) # 43

prompt: The fruit shop shipped 80kg of pears, and the number of apples shipped was 1/4 more than that of pears. How many kg of apples were shipped?
summary: var1 = [find](weight of pears shipped) #80, var2 = [find](percentage increase of apples from pears) #1/4, var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 80 * 1/4 = 20, var4 = [add](var1, var3) # 80 + 20 = 100, [return](var4) # 100

prompt: The store sells 200 kilograms of flour, and 4 times as much rice as flour. How many kilograms of flour and rice are sold in total?
summary: var1 = [find](amount of flour) #200, var2 = [find](amount of rice relative to flour) #4, var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 200 x 4 = 800, var4 = [add](var1,var3) # 200 + 800 = 1000, [return](var4) # 1000

prompt: The original price of a book is 20 yuan, and the price is now reduced by 25%. How much should I pay for this book?
summary: var1 = [find](original price of book) # 20, var2 = [find](percentage discount) # 25%, var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 20 * 0.25 = 5, var4 = [subtract](var1, var3) # 20 - 5 = 15, [return](var4) # 15

prompt: There are 360 ​​peach trees in the orchard, each of which is a peach tree (3/4) and an apple tree (2/3). How many apple trees are there?
summary: var1 = [find](total number of trees) #360, var2 = [multiply](var1, (3/4)) # 360 * (3/4) = 270, var3 = [find](proportion of apple trees) #(2/3), var4 = [divide](var2, var3) # 270 / (2/3) = 405, [return](var4) # 405

prompt: 375 kilograms of apples are harvested in the orchard, and these apples are put into 9 baskets on average, leaving 15 kilograms. How many kilograms of apples are in each basket?
summary: var1 = [find](total weight of harvested apples) #375, var2 = [find](number of baskets) #9, var3 = [subtract](var1, 15) # 375 - 15 = 360, var4 = [divide](var3, var2) # 360 / 9 = 40, [return](var4) # 40

prompt: The original cost of a certain product is 150 yuan. After technological reform, the cost is now reduced by 18%. How much is the current cost?
summary: var1 = [find](original cost) #150, var2 = [find](discount percentage) #18, var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 150 * 0.18 = 27, var4 = [subtract](var1, var3) # 150 - 27 = 123, [return](var4) # 123

prompt: Xiao Ming and Xiao Gang start from home at the same time to go to school, and walk toward each other. Xiao Ming walks 60 meters per minute, and Xiao Gang walks 50 meters per minute. Eighteen minutes later, the two met at school. How far is the distance between Xiao Ming and Xiao Gang's homes?
summary: var1 = [find](Xiao Ming's walking speed in meters per minute) #60, var2 = [find](Xiao Gang's walking speed in meters per minute) #50, var3 = [find](time elapsed before they met) #18, var4 = [multiply]([add](var1, var2), var3) # (60 + 50) * 18 = 1980, [return](var4) # 1980

prompt: A vegetable farm transported 130 kg of Chinese cabbage in the morning, and 50 kg more than twice as much in the morning in the afternoon. How many kilograms of Chinese cabbage did the supermarket transport less in the morning than in the afternoon?
summary: var1 = [find](amount of Chinese cabbage transported in the morning) #130, var2 = [find](twice the amount of Chinese cabbage transported in the morning) #2, [multiply](var1, var2) # 130 * 2 = 260, var3 = [add](var1, var2) # 260 + 50 = 310, var4 = [subtract](var3, var1) # 310 - 130 = 180, [return](var4) # 180

prompt: During the winter camp, the school has hired 3 vehicles, each of which can accommodate 42 students. After arriving at the destination, every 6 students are divided into an activity group. How many activity groups are there in total?
summary: var1 = [find](number of vehicles) #3, var2 = [find](capacity of each vehicle) #42, var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 3 * 42 = 126, var4 = [divide](var3, 6) # 126 / 6 = 21, [return](var4) # 21

prompt: The students planted trees, divided the number of people who dug holes by 5, and added 6, which happened to be the number of people who watered, and there were 18 people who watered. How many people were digging the pit?
summary: var1 = [find](number of people watering) #18, var2 = [find](number of people watering) #6, var3 = [subtract](var1, var2) # 18 - 6 = 12, var4 = [multiply](var3, 5) # 12 * 5 = 60, [return](var4) # 60

prompt: How much interest, in dollars, will you pay on an 8100 dollars loan for 1 year if the interest rate is 15%?
summary: var1 = [find](amount of loan) #8100, var2 = [find](interest rate) #15%, var3 = [divide](var2, 100) # 15 / 100 = 0.15, var4 = [multiply](var1, var3) # 8100 * 0.15 = 1215, [return](var4) # 1215

prompt: The current price of a padded jacket is 120 yuan, which is (1/4) lower than the original price. How much is the original price of this jacket?
summary: var1 = [find](current price of jacket) #120, var2 = [find](percentage of decrease) #(1/4), var3 = [subtract](1, var2) # 1 - (1/4) = 3/4, var4 = [divide](var1, var3) # 120 / (3/4) = 160, [return](var4) # 160

prompt: Mingming’s family used 150 kWh of electricity last month, and this month saved (1/6) compared with last month. How many kWh did they use this month?
summary: var1 = [find](kWh used last month) #150, var2 = [find](savings ratio) #1/6, var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 150 * 1/6 = 25, var4 = [subtract](var1, var3) # 150 - 25 = 125, [return](var4) # 125

prompt: The school clothing factory imported 240 meters of cloth to make school uniforms. Make a set of 2.5 meters of school cloth, and there will be 65 meters left after finishing. How many sets of school uniforms are there in total?
summary: var1 = [find](total meters of cloth) #240, var2 = [find](meters of cloth used for 1 set of uniform) #2.5, var3 = [subtract](var1, var4) # 240 - 65 = 175, var4 = [divide](var3, var2) # 175 / 2.5 = 70, [return](var4) # 70

prompt: Xiaogang has a science and technology book with 60 pages in total. He read the whole book (1/5) on the first day and 60% of the whole book on the second day. How many pages did he read in two days?
summary: var1 = [find](total pages in book) #60, var2 = [multiply](var1, 1/5) # 60 * (1/5) = 12, var3 = [multiply](var1, 60/100) # 60 * (60/100) = 36, var4 = [add](var2, var3) # 12 + 36 = 48, [return](var4) # 48

prompt: The young pioneers of a certain school collected tree species, the fourth grade collected (1/2) kilograms, the fifth grade collected (1/3) more kilograms than the fourth grade, and the sixth grade collected (6/5) the fifth grade. How many kilograms of tree species does the sixth grade collect?
summary: var1 = [find](kilograms collected by 4th grade) #(1/2), var2 = [find](additional kilograms collected by 5th grade) #(1/3), var3 = [add](var1, var2) # (1/2) + (1/3) = (5/6), var4 = [multiply](var3, (6/5)) # (5/6) * (6/5) = 1, [return](var4) # 1

prompt: The original price of a TV set is 2,500 yuan, and now the price is reduced by (1/5). How much is the price now?
summary: var1 = [find](original price of TV set) #2500, var2 = [find](fractional reduction) #1/5, var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 2500 * 1/5 = 500, var4 = [subtract](var1, var3) # 2500 - 500 = 2000, [return](var4) # 2000

prompt: There are 757 pounds of sand to be filled into bags. If each bag has a capacity of 65 pounds, how many bags are needed?
summary: var1 = [find](sand to be filled) # 757, var2 = [find](capacity of bag) # 65, var3 = [divide](var1, var2) # 757 / 65 = 11.71, var3 = [round_up](var3) # round up(11.71) = 12, [return](var3) # 12

prompt: Happy Fruit Store bought back 150 kg of apples and 73 kg of pears. The quantity of watermelons bought back is 4 times the total number of apples and pears. How many kilograms of watermelons are bought back by fruit shops?
summary: var1 = [find](amount of apples bought back) #150, var2 = [find](amount of pears bought back) #73, var3 = [add](var1, var2) # 150 + 73 = 223, var4 = [multiply](var3, 4) # 223 * 4 = 892, [return](var4) # 892

prompt: Xiaoyang uses 1.5 meters of cloth to make a jacket, and 2/3 of the cloth to make a pair of trousers. How many meters does Xiaoyang use to make a suit of clothes?
summary: var1 = [find](amount of cloth used for a jacket) #1.5, var2 = [find](fraction of cloth used for trousers) #2/3, var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 1.5 x 2/3 = 1, var4 = [add](var1, var3) # 1.5 + 1 = 2.5, [return](var4) # 2.5

prompt: Adam was painting a picture frame. The frame was 6 inches wide and 9 inches tall. What is the perimeter of the picture frame?
summary: var1 = [find](width) # 6, var2 = [find](height) # 9, var3 = [add](var1, var2), var4 = [add](var3, var3) # (6 + 9) * 2 = 30, [return](var4) # 30

prompt: A school used 320 kWh of electricity last month, and this month saved 5% compared with last month. How many kWh of electricity is used this month?
summary: var1 = [find](kWh of electricity used last month) #320, var2 = [find](percentage saved compared to last month) #5%, var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) #320 * 5% = 16, var4 = [subtract](var1, var3) #320 - 16 = 304, [return](var4) #304

prompt: The school has 120 soccer balls, which is 12 more than volleyball (4/5). How many volleyball balls are there?
summary: var1 = [find](number of soccer balls) #120, var2 = [find](proportion of volleyball balls in relation to soccer balls) #4/5, var3 = [subtract](var1, 12) # 120 - 12 = 108, var4 = [divide](var3, var2) # 108 / (4/5) = 135, [return](var4) # 135

prompt: The number of chickens raised by Xiao Ming is four times that of ducks, and there are 45 ducks. How many chickens and ducks are there altogether?
summary: var1 = [find](number of ducks) #45, var2 = [find](multiplier of chickens) #4, var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 45 * 4 = 180, var4 = [add](var1, var3) # 45 + 180 = 225, [return](var4) # 225

prompt: The road was built on Shengli North Road. In the first 5 days, a total of 2,854 meters was built, and then 3 days later, 510 meters were built every day. How many meters were built in total?
summary: var1 = "Shengli North Road", var2 = [find](total meters built in first 5 days) #2854, var3 = [find](meters built per day after first 5 days) #510, var4 = [multiply](3, var3) # 3 * 510 = 1530, var5 = [add](var2, var4) # 2854 + 1530 = 4384, [return](var5) # 4384

prompt: A car transports 290 boxes of bread, and after delivering them to 7 retail stores, there are 10 boxes left. How many boxes are delivered to each retail store on average?
summary: var1 = [find](number of boxes of bread) #290, var2 = [find](number of retail stores) #7, var3 = [subtract](var1, 10) # 290 - 10 = 280, var4 = [divide](var3, var2) # 280 / 7 = 40, [return](var4) # 40

prompt: There are 457 locust trees in the forest, and mulberry trees are 169 fewer than locust trees. How many locust trees and mulberry trees are there in the forest?
summary: var1 = [find](number of locust trees) #457, var2 = [find](difference between number of mulberry and locust trees) #169, var3 = [subtract](var1, var2) # 457 - 169 = 288, var4 = [add](var1, var3) # 457 + 288 = 745, [return](var4) # 745

prompt: A chemical fertilizer factory used 160 tons of coal last month, but this month it saved 30% compared to last month. How many tons of coal did it actually use this month?
summary: var1 = [find](amount of coal used last month) #160, var2 = [find](savings percentage) #30%, var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 160 * 0.3 = 48, var4 = [subtract](var1, var3) # 160 - 48 = 112, [return](var4) # 112

prompt: There were 6,000 primary school graduates in our city last year, and this year it is more than last year (1/20). How many people are graduating from elementary school this year?
summary: var1 = [find](number of primary school graduates last year) # 6000, var2 = [find](increase percentage) # 1/20, var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 6000 * (1/20) = 300, var4 = [add](var1, var3) # 6000 + 300 = 6300, [return](var4) # 6300

prompt: There are 80 gray cranes by the lake, four times the number of white cranes. How many white cranes and gray cranes are there in total?
summary: var1 = [find](number of gray cranes) #80, var2 = [find](multiplier for white cranes) #4, var3 = [divide](var1, var2) # 80 / 4 = 20, var4 = [add](var1, var3) # 80 + 20 = 100, [return](var4) # 100

prompt: A table costs 120 yuan and a chair costs 30 yuan. The company bought 32 sets of tables and chairs. How much did it cost in total?
summary: var1 = [find](cost of table) #120, var2 = [find](cost of chair) #30, var3 = [find](number of sets purchased) #32, var4 = [multiply](var1 + var2) # (120 + 30) * 32 = 4800, [return](var4) #4800

prompt: You can buy 3 sweaters for the price of one coat, and one coat costs 420 yuan. How much is a sweater cheaper than a coat?
summary: var1 = [find](cost of one coat) #420, var2 = [multiply](var1, 3) # 420 * 3 = 1260, var3 = [divide](var1, 3) # 420 / 3 = 140, var4 = [subtract](var1, var3) # 420 - 140 = 280, [return](var4) # 280

prompt: There are 13 giant pandas, 31 tigers, and 16 peacocks in the zoo. How many more tigers than peacocks?
summary: var1 = [find](number of giant pandas) #13, var2 = [find](number of tigers) #31, var3 = [find](number of peacocks) #16, var4 = [subtract](var2, var3) # 31 - 16 = 15, [return](var4) # 15

prompt: There are 32 students in the class. The teacher divided them into 5 equal groups. How many students are there in each group?
summary: var1 = [find](students) # 32, var2 = [find](groups) # 5, var3 = [divide](var1, var2) # 32 / 5 = 6.4, var3 = [round](var3) # [round](6.4) = 6, [return](var3) # 6

prompt: At an ice cream shop the ratio of sugar cones sold to waffle cones sold is 5:4. If there are 45 sugar cones sold, how many waffles cones would be sold?
summary: var1 = [find](sugar cones) # 45, var2 = [divide](var1, 5), var3 = [multiply](var2, 4 + 5) # (45 / 5) * (4 + 5) = 54, var4 = [divide](var3, 9) # 54 / 9 = 6, [return](var4) # 6

prompt: Jane can arrange 16 vases of flowers in a day. If there are 248 vases of flowers to be arranged, how many days are needed for her to finish all the flower arrangements?
summary: var1 = [find](vases of flowers to arrange) # 248, var2 = [find](vases per day) # 16, var3 = [divide](var1, var2) # 248 / 16 = 15.5, var3 = [round_up](var3) # round up(15.5) = 16, [return](var3) # 16

prompt: An orchard harvested 95 tons of apples last year. This year’s output is 20% more than last year. How many tons of apples can it harvest this year?
summary: var1 = [find](last year's apple output) #95, var2 = [find](increase percentage) #20, var3 = [multiply](var1, var2/100) # 95 * 20/100 = 19, var4 = [add](var1, var3) # 95 + 19 = 114, [return](var4) # 114

prompt: Uncle Zhang practiced shooting. He fired a total of 40 bullets, with a hit rate of 80%. How many bullets missed the target?
summary: var1 = [find](total number of bullets fired) #40, var2 = [find](hit rate as decimal) #0.8, var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 40 * 0.8 = 32, var4 = [subtract](var1, var3) # 40 - 32 = 8, [return](var4) # 8

prompt: Mr. Wang bought a brand phone at a mobile phone store for 1,600 yuan, which is 20% cheaper than the original price. How much is the original price?
summary: var1 = [find](price Mr. Wang paid) #1600, var2 = [find](discount percentage) #20%, var3 = [find](100% - discount percentage) #80%, var4 = [divide](var1, var3) # 1600 / 0.8 = 2000, [return](var4) # 2000

prompt: 19 children take a minibus to the zoo. They are to sit 2 or 3 to a seat. There are 7 seats. How many seats will have 3 children seated on them?
summary: var1 = [find](children) # 19, var2 = [find](seats) # 7, var3 = [divide](var1, var2) # 19 / 7 = 2.714 (rounded down to 2), var4 = [subtract](var1, var3 * var2) # 19 - (2 * 7) = 5, [return](var4) # 5

prompt: For the first main dish, they were asked to cook steak. If the third and second team cooked 240 plates of steak. And the first team cooked 75 plates less than what the second and third team made, how many steaks did they cook altogether?
summary: var2 = [find](number of steaks cooked by team 2 and 3) # 240, var3 = [find](number of steaks less cooked by team 1) # 75, var1 = [subtract](var2, var3) # 240 - 75 = 165, var2 = [add](var1, var2) # 165 + 240 = 405, [return](var2) # 405

prompt: There are 21 apricot trees and 27 pear trees in the orchard. The number of peach trees is the sum of apricot trees and pear trees (2/3). How many peach trees are there?
summary: var1 = [find](number of apricot trees) #21, var2 = [find](number of pear trees) #27, var3 = [add](var1, var2), var4 = [multiply](var3, 2/3) # (21 + 27) x (2/3) = 32, [return](var4) # 32

prompt: Our school originally planned to use 180 tons of coal per month, but the actual monthly saving is (2/15) lower than the plan. How many tons of coal is actually used per month?
summary: var1 = [find](Planned amount of coal per month) #180, var2 = [find](Ratio of actual saving to planned amount) #(2/15), var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 180 * (2/15) = 24, var4 = [subtract](var1, var3) # 180 - 24 = 156, [return](var4) # 156

prompt: Schools set up interest groups. There are 36 people in the art group, and the dance group has more people (1/4) than the art group. How many people are there in the dance group?
summary: var1 = [find](number of people in art group) #36, var2 = [find](multiplier for dance group) #1/4, var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 36 * (1/4) = 9, var4 = [add](var1, var3) # 36 + 9 = 45, [return](var4) # 45

prompt: A red ribbon is 30 meters long, and a yellow ribbon is (1/6) longer than the red ribbon. How long is the yellow ribbon in meters?
summary: var1 = [find](length of red ribbon) #30, var2 = [find](increase factor of yellow ribbon) #(1/6), var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 30 * (1/6) = 5, var4 = [add](var1, var3) # 30 + 5 = 35, [return](var4) # 35

prompt: Joan found 72 seashells and 12 starfishes on the beach. She gave Alyssa some of her seashells. She has 28 seashells. How many seashells did she give to Alyssa?
summary: var1 = [find](number of seashells found by Joan) #72, var2= [find](number of starfishes found by Joan) #12, var3= [find](seashells Joan has now) #28, var4 = [subtract](var1, var3) # 72 - 28 = 44, [return](var4) # 44

prompt: After the price of each tape recorder is reduced by 30%, the price is 350 yuan. How much is the original price of this tape recorder?
summary: var1 = [find](reduced price of tape recorder) #350, var2 = [find](percentage reduction) #30%, var3 = [divide](var2, 100) # 30/100 = 0.3, var4 = [multiply](var1, 1/(1-var3)) # 350 / (1-0.3) = 500, [return](var4) # 500

prompt: While on vacation, Debby took 24 pictures at the zoo and 12 at the museum. If she later deleted 14 of the pictures, how many pictures from her vacation did she still have?
summary: var1 = [find](zoo pictures) # 24, var2 = [find](museum pictures) # 12, var3 = [add](var1, var2) # 24 + 12 = 36, var4 = [subtract](var3, 14) # 36 - 14 = 22, [return](var4) # 22

prompt: Mike invited 13 friends to a birthday party, but 7 couldn't come. If he wanted to buy enough cupcakes so each person could have exactly 4, how many should he buy?
summary: var1 = [find](number of friends invited) #13, var2 = [find](number of friends who couldn't come) #7, var3 = [subtract](var1, var2) # 13 - 7 = 6, var4 = [multiply](var3, 4) # 6 * 4 = 24, [return](var4) # 24

prompt: There are 63 students in class 6(1), among which the number of boys is 4/5 of the number of girls. How many girls are there?
summary: var1 = [find](total number of students) #63, var2 = [find](ratio of boys to girls) #4/5, var3 = variable for number of girls, var4 = [divide](1, [add](1, var2)) # 1 / (1 + 4/5) = 5/9, var5 = [multiply](var1, var4) # 63 * 5/9 = 35, [return](var5) # 35

prompt: 1500 kilograms of peaches are transported from the orchard, and the quantity of apples transported is 4 times that of peaches. How many kilograms of peaches and apples are transported together?
summary: var1 = [find](weight of peaches) #1500, var2 = [find](multiplier for apples) #4, var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 1500 * 4 = 6000, var4 = [add](var1, var3) # 1500 + 6000 = 7500, [return](var4) # 7500

prompt: A production team produced a batch of parts, and produced 180 in the first 6 days. According to this calculation, it took another 15 days to produce. How many parts are there in this batch?
summary: var1 = [find](number of parts produced in first 6 days) #180, var2 = [find](number of days to produce entire batch) #6+15 = 21, var3 = [divide](var1, 6) # 180 / 6 = 30, var4 = [multiply](var3, 21) # 30 * 21 = 630, [return](var4) # 630

prompt: The rice yield of millet is about 70%. How many kilograms of millet are needed to produce 840 kilograms of rice?
summary: var1 = [find](percentage of rice yield for millet) #70%, var2 = [find](kilograms of rice needed) #840, var3 = [divide](var2, var1), var4 = [multiply](var3, 100) # (840 / 70) * 100 = 1200, [return](var4) # 1200

prompt: Wang Yong went to the stationery store and first bought a diary for 30 yuan, and then bought 3 ballpoint pens of the same type for 18 yuan. How much is each diary more expensive than each ballpoint pen?
summary: var1 = [find](cost of diary) #30, var2 = [find](total cost of pens) #18, var3 = [divide](var2, 3), #  18 / 3 = 6, var4 = [subtract](var1, var3), #  30 - 6 = 24, [return](var4) #24

prompt: A vegetable field has a total of 1.8 hectares. (1/3) of it is planted with green vegetables, and the rest are planted with radishes and spinach. The area ratio of radishes and spinach is 2:1. How many hectares are planted with radishes?
summary: var1 = [find](total area of vegetable field) #1.8, var2 = [multiply](var1, (1/3)) # 1.8 * (1/3) = 0.6, var3 = [subtract](var1, var2) # 1.8 - 0.6 = 1.2, var4 = [multiply](var3, (2/3)) # 1.2 * (2/3) = 0.8, [return](var4) # 0.8

prompt: The original cost of a suit of clothing is 160 yuan, but due to technological innovation, the cost has been reduced by 20%. How much does each set cost now?
summary: var1 = [find](original cost of suit) #160, var2 = [find](percentage decrease) #20%, var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 160 * 0.2 = 32, var4 = [subtract](var1, var3) # 160 - 32 = 128, [return](var4) # 128

prompt: Four times of 4.5 is 1.8 more than 1.2 times of a number. Find this number.
summary: var1 = [find](4 times 4.5) # 18, var2 = [find](1.2 times unknown number), var3 = [add](var2, 1.8), var4 = [divide](var3, 4) # (1.2 * X) + 1.8 = 18, 1.2X + 1.8 = 18, 1.2X = 16.2, X = 13.5, [return](X) # 13.5

prompt: Li Ming's home is 60 kilometers away from the county seat. In the past, it took 4 hours to reach the county seat by bicycle. Now by car, an average of 90 kilometers per hour. How many times faster is the car than the bicycle?
summary: var1 = [find](distance to county seat) #60, var2 = [find](speed of bicycle) #60/4 = 15, var3 = [find](speed of car) #90, var4 = [divide](var3, var2) # 90 / 15 = 6, [return](var4) # 6

prompt: A piece of clothing is priced at 200 yuan after a 20% price reduction. How much is the price of this clothing before the price reduction?
summary: var1 = [find](price of clothing after reduction) #200, var2 = [find](percent of reduction) #20, var3 = [divide](var2, 100) # 20 / 100 = 0.2, var4 = [multiply](var1, (1 + var3)) # 200 / (1 - 0.2) = 250, [return](var4) # 250

prompt: The number of students who meet the sports standards in Guangming Primary School accounts for (3/5) of the total number of students in the school, which is exactly 270. How many students are there in the school?
summary: var1 = [find](proportion of students meeting sports standards) #3/5, var2 = [find](total number of students in school) #unknown, var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) # (3/5) * var2 = 270, var2 = [divide](270, var1) # 270 / (3/5) = 450, [return](var2) # 450

prompt: The factory used to manufacture 1,800 machine parts every day, but now the number of parts manufactured every day is 10% less than before. How many machine parts are manufactured every day?
summary: var1 = [find](number of parts manufactured per day before decrease) #1800, var2 = [find](percentage decrease) #10%, var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 1800 * 0.1 = 180, var4 = [subtract](var1,var3) # 1800 - 180 = 1620, [return](var4) # 1620

prompt: Scott has 4 tickets. Ernest has 9 tickets. Ernest finds another 72. How many tickets does Ernest end with?
summary: var1 = [find](number of tickets Scott has) #4, var2 = [find](number of tickets Ernest has) #9, var3 = [find](added tickets found by Ernest) #72, var4 = [add](var2, var3) #9 + 72 = 81, [return](var4) #81

prompt: Huayuan Primary School bought 35 sets of desks and chairs for one person, each desk is 118 yuan, and each chair is 42 yuan. How much does it cost in total?
summary: var1 = [find](number of sets) # 35, var2 = [find](cost of one desk) # 118, var3 = [find](cost of one chair) # 42, var4 = [multiply](var1, [add](var2, var3)) # 35 * (118 + 42) = 5600, [return](var4) # 5600

prompt: A swimming pool is 50 meters long, 12 meters wide and 2.5 meters deep. How many cubic meters of water can it hold after it is filled with water?
summary: var1 = [find](length of swimming pool) #50, var2 = [find](width of swimming pool) #12, var3 = [find](depth of swimming pool) #2.5, var4 = [multiply](var1, var2, var3) # 50 * 12 * 2.5 = 1500, [return](var4) # 1500

prompt: Xiaohua’s family has a bucket of mineral water, totaling 16 kilograms. On the first day, 1/10 of the whole bucket of water is used, and on the second day, 12.5% ​​of the whole bucket of water is used. How many kilograms of water are used in two days?
summary: var1 = [find](total weight of mineral water in the bucket) # 16, var2 = [multiply](var1, 1/10) # 16 * 1/10 = 1.6, var3 = [multiply](var1, 12.5/100) # 16 * 12.5/100 = 2, var4 = [add](var2, var3) # 1.6 + 2 = 3.6, [return](var4) # 3.6

prompt: A project can be completed by A alone in 12 hours, and B can only complete (4/5) of the project in the same time. How many hours can B alone complete the whole project?
summary: var1 = [find](time for A to complete project) #12, var2 = [find](percentage of project completed by B alone) #(4/5), var3 = [divide](1, var2) # [divide](1, 4/5) = 1.25, var4 = [multiply](var1, var3) # 12 * 1.25 = 15, [return](var4) # 15

prompt: The water content in a child's body is about 78% of his body weight. Xiao Hua's weight is 35 kg. What is the approximate water content in his body = how many kg?
summary: var1 = [find](Xiao Hua's weight) #35, var2 = [find](water content percentage) #78%, var3 = [divide](var2,100) # 78 / 100 = 0.78, var4 = [multiply](var1, var3) # 35 x 0.78 = 27.3, [return](var4) # 27.3

prompt: Noah made 12 kg of trail mix for his family's hiking trip. His family ate 8600 g of the trail mix on the hiking trip. How many grams of trail mix did Noah have left?
summary: var1 = [find](trail mix made) # 12 kg, var2 = [convert](var1, g) # 12 kg * 1000 g/kg = 12000 g, var3 = [find](trail mix eaten) # 8600 g, var4 = [subtract](var2, var3) # 12000 g - 8600 g = 3400 g, [return](var4) # 3400 g

prompt: Before lunch a waitress had already earned $5 in tips. After lunch she had 7 customers and each customer gave her a 2 dollar tip. How much money did she earn total?
summary: var1 = [find](earnings before lunch) # 5, var2 = [find](tips after lunch) # 7, var3 = [find](tip per customer) # 2, var2 = var2 * var3 # 7 * 2 = 14, var1 = [add](var1, var2) # 5 + 14 = 19, [return](var1) # 19

prompt: A computer of a certain brand originally sold for 7,000 yuan each, but now the price has been reduced by 1/5. How much is the current price of each computer?
summary: var1 = [find](original price of computer) # 7000, var2 = [find](reduction in price) # 1/5, var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 7000 * (1/5) = 1400, var4 = [subtract](var1, var3) # 7000 - 1400 = 5600, [return](var4) # 5600

prompt: The coal factory has 400 tons of coal, 25% of the total is shipped in the morning, and 40% of the total is shipped in the afternoon. How many tons more are shipped in the afternoon than in the morning?
summary: var1 = [find](total amount of coal) #400, var2 = [multiply](var1, 0.25) # 400 * 0.25 = 100 (tons shipped in morning), var3 = [multiply](var1, 0.40) # 400 * 0.40 = 160 (tons shipped in afternoon), var4 = [subtract](var3, var2) # 160 - 100 = 60, [return](var4) # 60

prompt: The school library bought a batch of new books. Among them, there are 126 popular science books, which is exactly three times that of comic books. How many books are there in total?
summary: var1 = [find](number of popular science books) #126, var2 = [find](ratio of popular science books to comic books) #3:1, var3 = [divide](var1, var2) # 126 / 3 = 42, var4 = [multiply](var3, 4) # 42 * 4 = 168, [return](var4) # 168

prompt: The school planted 50 trees, and the survival rate was 90%. How many trees survived?
summary: var1 = [find](number of trees planted) #50, var2 = [find](survival rate as a percentage) #90%, var3 = [divide](var2, 100) # 90 / 100 = 0.9, var4 = [multiply](var1, var3) # 50 * 0.9 = 45, [return](var4) #45

prompt: Xiaogang has a storybook with 60 pages in total. He read the whole book (1/5) on the first day and 40% of the book on the second day. How many pages did he read in total in two days?
summary: var1 = [find](number of pages in the storybook) #60, var2 = [multiply](var1, (1/5)) # 60 * (1/5) = 12, var3 = [multiply](var1, 0.4) # 60 * 0.4 = 24, var4 = [add](var2, var3) # 12 + 24 = 36, [return](var4) # 36

prompt: The supermarket shipped 300 kilograms of cucumbers, which is 25% less than the shipment of tomatoes. How many kilograms of tomatoes were shipped?
summary: var1 = [find](kilograms of cucumbers) #300, var2 = [subtract](100, 25), var3 = [divide](var2, 100), # calculate the percentage left as a decimal = (100 - 25) / 100 = 0.75, var4 = [divide](var1, var3) # 300 / 0.75 = 400, [return](var4) # 400

prompt: Naval Elementary School holds a third-grade parent-teacher meeting. Each row can seat 32 people. After sitting in 8 rows, there are 46 parents who have no seats. How many parents will participate in the parent-teacher meeting?
summary: var1 = [find](number of seats per row) #32, var2 = [multiply](var1, 8) # 32 * 8 = 256, var3 = [find](number of parents with no seats) #46, var4 = [add](var2, var3) # 256 + 46 = 302, [return](var4) # 302

prompt: Joan grew 29 carrots and 14 watermelons. Jessica grew 11 carrots. How many carrots did they grow in all?
summary: var1 = [find](number of carrots grown by Joan) #29, var2 = [find](number of watermelons grown by Joan) #14, var3 = [find](number of carrots grown by Jessica) #11, var4 = [add](var1, var3) # 29 + 11 = 40, [return](var4) # 40

prompt: The per capita income of farmers in Xingfu Village last year was 2150 yuan, which increased (1/10) this year compared to last year. What is the per capita income this year?
summary: var1 = [find](per capita income of farmers in Xingfu Village last year) #2150, var2 = [find](increase percentage) #(1/10), var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 2150 * (1/10) = 215, var4 = [add](var1, var3) # 2150 + 215 = 2365, [return](var4) # 2365

prompt: She had 35 mistletoe stickers and wanted to place them equally in 8 cards. How many mistletoe stickers will she have left?
summary: var1 = [find](mistletoe stickers) # 35, var2 = [find](cards) # 8, var3 = [divide](var1, var2) # 35 / 8 = 4 with a remainder of 3, var4 = [find](remainder) # 3, [return](var4) # 3

prompt: Qiangqiang bought 4 pieces of the same undershirt for 100 yuan, and there is 12 yuan left. How much is each such undershirt?
summary: var1 = [find](total cost of 4 undershirts) #100, var2 = [find](amount of money left) #12, var3 = [subtract](var1, var2) # 100 - 12 = 88, var4 = [divide](var3, 4) # 88 / 4 = 22, [return](var4) # 22

prompt: There are 120 books in the fifth grade, which is exactly (1/14) of the total number of books in the school. How many books does the school have?
summary: var1 = [find](number of books in fifth grade) #120, var2 = [find](fraction of books in fifth grade in relation to total books) #(1/14), var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 120 * (1/14) = 8.571, var4 = [divide](var1, var2) # 120 / (1/14) = 1680, [return](var4) # 1680

prompt: There are 800 hens in the chicken farm, and the number of roosters is 1/16 of that of hens. How many chickens are there in total in the chicken farm?
summary: var1 = [find](number of hens) #800, var2 = [find](number of roosters as fraction of hens) #1/16, var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 800 * 1/16 = 50, var4 = [add](var1, var3) # 800 + 50 = 850, [return](var4) # 850

prompt: Mr. Lee wants to load 134 tons of his fruits. A large truck can load 15 tons of fruits and small truck can load 7 tons. In order to use the least number of trucks and have every truck fully occupied, how many large trucks should be used?
summary: var1 = [find](tons of fruits) # 134, var2 = [find](large truck capacity) # 15, var3 = [divide](var1, var2) # 134 / 15 = 8.93, var3 = [round_down](var3) # round down(8.93) = 8, [return](var3) # 8

prompt: The current price of a coat is 98 yuan, which is 30% lower than the original price. How much is the original dress?
summary: var1 = [find](current price of coat) #98, var2 = [find](percentage decrease) #30%, var3 = [divide](var2, 100) # 30 / 100 = 0.3, var4 = [divide](var1, 1 - var3) # 98 / (1 - 0.3) = 140, [return](var4) # 140

prompt: The school held a hands-on ability competition, and there was a competition for tying ropes. On a 20-meter-long rope, tie a knot every 2 meters and leave no knots at both ends. How many knots should be tied in total?
summary: var1 = [find](length of rope) #20, var2 = [find](distance between knots) #2, var3 = [subtract](var1, 2) # 20 - 2 = 18, var4 = [divide](var3, var2) # 18 / 2 = 9, [return](var4) # 9

prompt: The price of a basketball is 60 yuan, and the price of a volleyball is that of a basketball (17/20). How much is a volleyball cheaper than a basketball?
summary: var1 = [find](price of basketball) # 60, var2 = [find](price of volleyball as fraction) # 17/20, var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 60 * 17/20 = 51, var4 = [subtract](var1, var3) # 60 - 51 = 9, [return](var4) # 9

prompt: The school held a spring sports meeting, and 56 students from the sixth grade participated. Among them (3/7) are female athletes. How many male athletes participated in the sports meeting?
summary: var1 = [find](total number of students who participated) #56, var2 = [find](fraction of female athletes) #(3/7), var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 56 * (3/7) = 24, var4 = [subtract](var1, var3) # 56 -24 = 32, [return](var4) # 32

prompt: In the reading activity, Xiaoqiang read a book with a total of 136 pages. He has read 25% of the book. How many pages are left?
summary: var1 = [find](Total number of pages in the book) #136, var2 = [find](Percentage of book already read) #25%, var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 136 x 0.25 = 34, var4 = [subtract](var1, var3) # 136 - 34 = 102, [return](var4) # 102

prompt: There are 56 boys and 35 girls in the second grade. The number of students in the sixth grade is 4 times the number of students in the second grade. How many people are there in the sixth grade?
summary: var1 = [find](number of boys in 2nd grade) #56, var2 = [find](number of girls in 2nd grade) #35, var3 = [add](var1, var2) # 56 + 35 = 91, var4 = [multiply](var3, 4) # 91 * 4 = 364, [return](var4) # 364

prompt: Xiaohong weighs 42 kilograms, Xiaoyun weighs 40 kilograms, and Xiaoxin weighs (1/2) their weight. How many kilograms does Xiaoxin weigh?

prompt: Sam had 7 pennies and 8 dimes in his bank. His sister borrowed 4 dimes. How many dimes does Sam have now?

prompt: Kate, Maggie, and Sue added up their ages. The total was 48. Kate is 19 and Maggie is 17. How old is Sue?

prompt: Faye and her mom were picking carrots from their garden. Faye picked 23 and her mother picked 5. If only 12 of the carrots were good, how many bad carrots did they have?
summary: var1 = [find](Faye carrots) # 23, var2 = [find](mom carrots) # 5, var3 = [add](var1, var2) # 23 + 5 = 28, var4 = [subtract](var3, 12) # 28 - 12 = 16, [return](var4) # 16

prompt: There are 890 peach trees in the orchard, which is 5 times that of pear trees. How many fruit trees are there in the orchard?

prompt: The original price of a stereo is 1,000 yuan, and the price is reduced (3/20) for sale. What is the current price?
summary: var1 = [find](original price of stereo) #1000, var2 = [find](fraction of price reduction) #3/20, var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 1000 * 3/20 = 150, var4 = [subtract](var1, var3) # 1000 - 150 = 850, [return](var4) # 850

prompt: An MP3 player costs 40 dollars. The sales tax is 2.4 dollars. What is the percent of sales tax?
summary: var1 = [find](cost of MP3 player) #40, var2 =  [find](sales tax) #2.4, var3 = [divide](var2, var1) # 2.4 / 40 = 0.06, var4 = [multiply](var3, 100) # 0.06 * 100 = 6, [return](var4) # 6

prompt: There are 22 orchid bushes and 40 orange trees currently in the park. Park workers will plant 13 orchid bushes today. How many orchid bushes will the park have when the workers are finished?

prompt: The original price of a bicycle is 300 yuan. This year, the price of this bicycle is reduced by 10%. How much does this bicycle cost this year?
summary: var1 = [find](original price of the bicycle) #300, var2 = [find](discount percentage) #10%, var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 300 * 0.1 = 30, var4 = [subtract](var1, var3) # 300 - 30 = 270, [return](var4) # 270

prompt: Measure the depth of the water with a bamboo pole. The part above the water is 120 cm long, which is 20 cm less than twice the part submerged in the water. How deep is the water in cm?
summary: var1 = [find](length of part above water) #120, var2 = [find](twice the part submerged in water) #var1 + 20, var3 = [subtract](var2, var1) # var2 - var1 = 20 + 120 = 140, var4 = [divide](var3, 2) # 140 / 2 = 70, [return](var4) # 70

prompt: During the energy-saving and emission-reduction activities, the "Environmental Guardians" of the Experimental Primary School recycled 800 kilograms of waste paper. It is known that the non-renewable rate of waste paper is 20%. How many kilograms of recycled paper can be produced from the recycled waste paper?
summary: var1 = [find](waste paper recycled) #800, var2 = [find](non-renewable rate) #20%, var3 = [multiply](var1, var2/100) # 800 * 20/100 = 160, var4 = [subtract](var1, var3) # 800 - 160 = 640, [return](var4) # 640

prompt: The TV factory originally planned to produce a batch of TV sets in 20 days, but actually produced 25 sets a day, and completed the task 4 days ahead of schedule. How many TV sets are there in this batch?
